description: From Latin intempestīvus, from in- + tempestīvus (“seasonable”).

adjectives.description: intempestive (comparative more intempestive, superlative most intempestive)

entries.meaning: (now rare) untimely, happening at an inappropriate moment
examples: Luxus funerum [display at funerals], shall be taken away, that intempestive expense moderated, and many others.
